  <refnamediv>
    <refname>FLhvsBoxSetValue</refname>
    <refpurpose>
      Sets the cursor position of a previously-declared FLhvsBox widget.
    </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      <emphasis>FLhvsBoxSetValue</emphasis> sets the cursor position of a previously-declared <link linkend="FLhvsBox"><citetitle>FLhvsBox</citetitle></link> widget.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Syntax</title>
    <synopsis><command>FLhvsBox</command> kx, ky, ihandle</synopsis>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Initialization</title>
    <para>
      <emphasis>ihandle</emphasis> – an integer number used a univocally-defined handle for identifying a specific HVS box (see below).
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Performance</title>
    <para>
      <emphasis>kx, ky</emphasis>– the coordinates of the HVS cursor position to be set.
    </para>
    <para>
      <emphasis>FLhvsBoxSetValue</emphasis> sets the cursor position of a previously-declared <link linkend="FLhvsBox"><citetitle>FLhvsBox</citetitle></link> widget. The <emphasis>kx</emphasis> and <emphasis>ky</emphasis> arguments, denoting the cursor position, have to be expressed in normalized values (0 to 1 range).
    </para>
    <para>
      See the entry for <link linkend="hvs2"><citetitle>hvs2</citetitle></link> for an example of usage of <emphasis>FLhvsBoxSetValue</emphasis>.</para>
  </refsect1>
